<TITLE> Man with bombs holds hostage in Habiganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Habiganj, July 8 (bdnews24.com) - A man with bombs strapped to his body was holding an employee hostage after storming into the district BTCL office on Wednesday, officials said. The hostage was named as sub-assistant engineer Arab Ali by his colleague Shirish Chandra Das, who managed to escape from the office. Das said the man entered the office with a child at around 5pm. RAB, police and fire service men surrounded the office, said deputy commissioner Abul Kashem Talukder, who was at the spot. Superintendent of police Mohammad Akkas Uddin was also present. bdn
